&gt; RFC 5988 very specifically says that they should not be treated as being
&gt; resolvable (first paragraph of http://tools.ietf.org/html/**
&gt; rfc5988#section-4.2 &lt;http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5988#section-4.2&gt;)


That&#39;s not my reading. For pragmatic reasons it says you shouldn&#39;t hammer
the server, but explicitly allows that they can:
&quot;point to a resource that contains a definition of the semantics of the
relation type&quot;

It actually seems quite close to RDF versus Linked Data. RDF says the
relationship should be a URI (and for years people used identifiers that
wouldn&#39;t resolve, even though they were defined by ontologies somewhere).
Linked Data says they should.

No one actually resolves the predicate every time they see it appear in
Linked Datasets.

Barry

